commitResults.messageTitle: Improve use case documentation for logs management
commitResults.messageBody:
Previous set of use cases for `addlog`, `editlog` and `deletelog`
features did not provide guarantees, descriptions of certain relevant UI
interactions, referred to "friends" as "contacts" and at points
referenced unnecessary UI details like specific commands.

This commit thus implements the following changes:
* Change references to "contacts" as "friends"
* Include guarantees in use cases where relevant
* Improve phrasing to reflect "intent" and "action" of a given actor
* Improve phrasing to reflect greater clarity in general

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG - minor issues in Log Management
Add base classes for Log and UniqueLogList
commitResults.messageBody:
Added classes and their unit tests for Log and UniqueLogList classes for
use in the model component to support logs functionality.

The key design point are:
1. Logs
	* Logs are considered identical if they have the same title.
	* Logs are considered equal if they have the same title AND
	  description.
	* The default description if no description is provided is an
	  empty string.

2. UniqueLogList
The unique log list is intended to be pointed to by a Person object,
such that each person has a list of logs. In this commit, basic list
functionalities of add, set, remove, contains have been added.

Future modifications to these two base classes will be for command-specific
functionalities.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Person class to include Logs
commitResults.messageBody:
Updated `Person` class to include `UniqueLogList` and `Log` to support
log features. Changes to `Person` class also meant corresponding changes
to test cases and sample data for unit testing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Storage component to support Logs
commitResults.messageBody:
Implemented `JsonAdapatedLogs` and updated `JsonAdaptedPerson` to
support saving of logs in the json file.

Updated unit and integration tests and test cases for `JsonAdaptedTest` and
`JsonSerializableAddressBookTest` to include logs in testing.

This is a big commit, plenty of changes, with the main aim to implement
all classes necessary for the addlog command. Notable classes
written/changes are:

* `AddLogCommand` class
* `AddLogCommand.AddLogDescriptor` class
* `AddLogCommandParser` class
* (Incomplete) unit and integration tests and test cases for the above three classes

The inclusion of the three classes integrates nicely into the existing
`Command` interface framework. A notable design choice was to use a
static nested `AddLogCommand.AddLogDescriptor` class, and the rationale
was to follow the analogous design in the `EditCommand` class, since it
was easily extendible and helped with cleaner encapsulation.

Note that test cases have not been fully completed and debugged.

In this commit:
* Unit and integration tests and test cases for the addlog feature and corresponding
  classes are completed and debugged.
* checkstyle violations are fixed.

Updated `AddressBookParser` and relevant test cases to support `addlog`
command. As with all other supported commands, will be called and
`CommandResult` object will be returned.

In this commit, support for `deletelog` feature has been added. Main
changes are described here:
1. implementation of `DeleteLogCommand` class.
2. implementation of `DeleteLogCommandParser` class.
3. appropriate extensions to `ArgumentMultiMap` and `AddressBookParser`
   classes to support new feature.

Main design choice to take note is the use of a nested
`DeleteLogDescriptor` in `DeleteLogCommand`, much like that in
`EditCommand` and `AddLogCommand`. The idea is to encapsulate details of
the deletion into the helper class so that encapsulation is cleaner and
SLAP is carried out as far as is reasonable.

Note that this commit is untested.

Completed unit tests for `DeleteLogCommandParser`. Note that integration
tests for `DeleteLogCommand` are incomplete.

First full set of unit and integration tests w.r.t. `Model` component
complete and debugged. Note that tests depend on `TypicalAddressBook`
testing utilities.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify `Person` constructor to handle non-name nulls
commitResults.messageBody:
Non-name fields are optional in a `Person` object. For cleaner
encapsulation and downstream tasks, I have moved the handling of null
arguments into the constructor, and accordingly modified the
`AddCommandParser` class.

It is cleaner to have specific constrcutors for specific reasons. So we
have two - a main one that can handle nulls, and one with only a name
argument, since it is being used for searching.

Note: will likely remove down the line, as we implement name-specific
operations.

Works by iterating through the address book and using the
`Person::isSamePerson` method to find the person, given a name.

Note: down the line, implementation should be changed to be based on
something like `Person::hasSameName`, since relying on `Person::isSamePerson` is
probably bad practice.

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, `editlog` did not correctly handle cases where a user edited
a log to be the same as an existing log, because the wrong equality
check method was called (duplicate checks were being done by logs having
same title AND description, which is not allowed).

This bug has been fixed and one test case has been added to verify the
behaviour.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG for log related things, misc.
Modify MainWindow to dynamically reload insights
commitResults.messageBody:
At show insights, previously no call was made to refresh the list when
the command was called. Now, the MainWindow component, when called to
switch tabs, will dynamically request for a new list from the logic
component.

As an aside, the proper way to do this is probably to have a
`UniqueInsightsList`, or alternatively to have a new field in
`CommandResult`, but both seem unnecessary given the time constraints.
